<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Using the initial infusion equation =
=E2=80=93 Strike Water Temperature Tw =3D (0.41 / R)(T2 =E2=80=93 T1) + T2 =
we would get the following.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">(0.41 / 2.5) x (67-18) + 67 =3D 75=C2=
=B0C</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">So we would need to heat our initial s=
trike water to 75=C2=B0C to hit our desired mash temperature of 67=C2=B0C.<=
